comments.body:
@promag @mysticaltech yeah, if you want to change the -conf or -datadir setting, then using BITCOIND_OPTS (probably by setting it in /etc/sysconfig/bitcoind) is the best way.

As for the --daemon option, I think that's correct for modern bitcoin exes. 
I'll try to give this a test on centos6 in the next couple of days.

